defs.docs:
CW20 is a specification for fungible tokens based on CosmWasm.
The name and design is loosely based on Ethereum's ERC20 standard,
but many changes have been made. The types in here can be imported by
contracts that wish to implement this spec, or by contracts that call
to any standard cw20 contract.

attributes.value:
*
CW20 is a specification for fungible tokens based on CosmWasm.
The name and design is loosely based on Ethereum's ERC20 standard,
but many changes have been made. The types in here can be imported by
contracts that wish to implement this spec, or by contracts that call
to any standard cw20 contract.

For more information on this specification, please check out the
[README](https://github.com/CosmWasm/cw-plus/blob/main/packages/cw20/README.md).
*/

defs.name: Url
defs.docs: A reference to an externally hosted logo. Must be a valid HTTP or HTTPS URL.

defs.name: Embedded
defs.docs: Logo content stored on the blockchain. Enforce maximum size of 5KB on all variants

defs.name: Logo
defs.docs: This is used for uploading logo data, or setting it in InstantiateData

defs.name: Svg
defs.docs:
Store the Logo as an SVG file. The content must conform to the spec
 at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scalable_Vector_Graphics
 (The contract should do some light-weight sanity-check validation)

defs.name: Png
defs.docs:
Store the Logo as a PNG file. This will likely only support up to 64x64 or so
 within the 5KB limit.

defs.name: EmbeddedLogo
defs.docs:
This is used to store the logo on the blockchain in an accepted format.
 Enforce maximum size of 5KB on all variants.

defs.name: Url
defs.docs: A reference to an externally hosted logo. Must be a valid HTTP or HTTPS URL.

defs.name: Embedded
defs.docs: There is an embedded logo on the chain, make another call to download it.

defs.name: LogoInfo
defs.docs:
This is used to display logo info, provide a link or inform there is one
 that can be downloaded from the blockchain itself

defs.name: Transfer
defs.docs: Transfer is a base message to move tokens to another account without triggering actions

defs.name: Burn
defs.docs: Burn is a base message to destroy tokens forever

defs.name: Send
defs.docs:
Send is a base message to transfer tokens to a contract and trigger an action
 on the receiving contract.

defs.name: IncreaseAllowance
defs.docs:
Only with "approval" extension. Allows spender to access an additional amount tokens
 from the owner's (env.sender) account. If expires is Some(), overwrites current allowance
 expiration with this one.

defs.name: DecreaseAllowance
defs.docs:
Only with "approval" extension. Lowers the spender's access of tokens
 from the owner's (env.sender) account by amount. If expires is Some(), overwrites current
 allowance expiration with this one.

defs.name: TransferFrom
defs.docs:
Only with "approval" extension. Transfers amount tokens from owner -> recipient
 if `env.sender` has sufficient pre-approval.

defs.name: SendFrom
defs.docs:
Only with "approval" extension. Sends amount tokens from owner -> contract
 if `env.sender` has sufficient pre-approval.

defs.name: BurnFrom
defs.docs: Only with "approval" extension. Destroys tokens forever

defs.name: Mint
defs.docs:
Only with the "mintable" extension. If authorized, creates amount new tokens
 and adds to the recipient balance.

defs.name: UpdateMinter
defs.docs:
Only with the "mintable" extension. The current minter may set
 a new minter. Setting the minter to None will remove the
 token's minter forever.

defs.name: UpdateMarketing
defs.docs:
Only with the "marketing" extension. If authorized, updates marketing metadata.
 Setting None/null for any of these will leave it unchanged.
 Setting Some("") will clear this field on the contract storage

defs.name: project
defs.docs: A URL pointing to the project behind this token.

defs.name: description
defs.docs: A longer description of the token and it's utility. Designed for tooltips or such

defs.name: marketing
defs.docs: The address (if any) who can update this data structure

defs.name: UploadLogo
defs.docs: If set as the "marketing" role on the contract, upload a new URL, SVG, or PNG for the token

defs.name: Cw20ExecuteMsg
Balance
defs.docs:
Returns the current balance of the given address, 0 if unset.
 Return type: BalanceResponse.

defs.name: TokenInfo
defs.docs:
Returns metadata on the contract - name, decimals, supply, etc.
 Return type: TokenInfoResponse.

defs.name: Allowance
defs.docs:
Only with "allowance" extension.
 Returns how much spender can use from owner account, 0 if unset.
 Return type: AllowanceResponse.

defs.name: Minter
defs.docs:
Only with "mintable" extension.
 Returns who can mint and the hard cap on maximum tokens after minting.
 Return type: MinterResponse.

defs.name: MarketingInfo
defs.docs:
Only with "marketing" extension
 Returns more metadata on the contract to display in the client:
 - description, logo, project url, etc.
 Return type: MarketingInfoResponse.

defs.name: DownloadLogo
defs.docs:
Only with "marketing" extension
 Downloads the embedded logo data (if stored on chain). Errors if no logo data stored for
 this contract.
 Return type: DownloadLogoResponse.

defs.name: AllAllowances
defs.docs:
Only with "enumerable" extension (and "allowances")
 Returns all allowances this owner has approved. Supports pagination.
 Return type: AllAllowancesResponse.

defs.name: AllAccounts
defs.docs:
Only with "enumerable" extension
 Returns all accounts that have balances. Supports pagination.
 Return type: AllAccountsResponse.

defs.name: Cw20QueryMsg
cap
defs.docs:
cap is a hard cap on total supply that can be achieved by minting.
 Note that this refers to total_supply.
 If None, there is unlimited cap.
